Class TadukooTable

java.lang.Object
java.awt.Component
java.awt.Container

javax.swing.JScrollPane
com.github.tadukoo.util.view.components.TadukooTable
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.ScrollPaneConstants
public class TadukooTable
extends javax.swing.JScrollPane
Tadukoo Table is an extension of JScrollPane that contains a JTable. It provides methods for using Tables of OrderedMappedPojos to populate the JTable and to make it easier to update the table.
Version:
Alpha v.0.2
Author:
Logan Ferree (Tadukoo)

    • setTableData

      public void setTableData​(Table<OrderedMappedPojo> data)
      Sets the columns and rows of the table based on the passed in data. If the key order was set on the Tadukoo Table, that key order will be used, otherwise the key order of the first pojo in the data will be used.
      Parameters:
      data - The pojos to use to populate the table
